==German==
===Etymology===
Compound of *''Diens'' and ''[[Tag]]'', calque of Latin ''[[dies Martis]]''. According to ''Kluge 23th. ed'' *''Diens'' corresponds to the Germanic god ''[[Thingsus]]''.
Another option is that Tuesday denoted the day on which the ''[[thing]]'' (court) was held.
===Noun===
'''Dienstag''' ''m''

# [[Tuesday]]

